{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"","closed_at":null,"closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"63560eaca4c73aa4dbcecfeed55427227831b8f0c497ab14cf3ba84b16d69343","created_at":"2026-03-02T12:19:57Z","created_by":"sling/refinery","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"## Bug Report\n\n### Command\n`gt mol step done \u003cstep-id\u003e`\n\n### Symptom\nStep closes successfully (✓ Closed step) but then fails with:\n```\nError: finding next steps: finding ready steps: parsing bd ready --mol output: json: cannot unmarshal object into Go value of type []*beads.Issue\n```\n\n### Impact\n- Steps ARE closed correctly (not blocked on this)\n- Auto-continuation breaks, requiring manual `gt mol progress` + `gt bead show` to find next step\n- Happens every single `gt mol step done` call (100% repro)\n- Observed during refinery patrol molecule (mol-refinery-patrol)\n\n### Workaround\nManually track progress: `gt mol progress \u003croot-bead-id\u003e` then `gt bead show \u003cnext-step-id\u003e`\n\n### Likely cause\n`bd ready --mol` output format has changed - returns an object where code expects array of issues.\n","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"sl-vrd","is_template":0,"issue_type":"bug","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"aron@asorman.io","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":1,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"open","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"gt mol step done: json unmarshal error on auto-continuation","updated_at":"2026-03-02T12:19:57Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"","closed_at":null,"closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"b492dcef3d7d57bdfe07f2923f7532f5c22c78395f67aa6db342eddee55a7b27","created_at":"2026-03-03T20:57:16Z","created_by":"mayor","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"When eclub witness/refinery does a handoff, the new session is named gt-witness/gt-refinery instead of ec-witness/ec-refinery, creating unregistered duplicate sessions. Root cause is in gastown handoff code: internal/cmd/handoff.go calls session.PrefixFor(rig) but resolves to default 'gt' prefix instead of eclub's configured 'ec' prefix. The session naming functions in internal/session/names.go are correct — the issue is in how the rig name is passed through the handoff flow, or how the prefix registry is initialized. See hq-1rj for full context. Fix: ensure PrefixFor() correctly resolves the rig prefix during handoff.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"sl-vxr","is_template":0,"issue_type":"bug","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"aron@asorman.io","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":1,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"open","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Fix handoff session naming: uses gt-* prefix instead of rig-specific prefix (ec-*)","updated_at":"2026-03-03T20:57:16Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
